1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,593
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,593 --> 00:00:03,036
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:04,653
(Kangsu Construction)

4
00:00:04,653 --> 00:00:06,173
(Episode 13)

5
00:00:06,173 --> 00:00:08,659
Having a Kangsu Construction employee ID
or not...

6
00:00:08,813 --> 00:00:09,910
makes all the difference.

7
00:00:12,059 --> 00:00:13,059
Hello.

8
00:00:14,032 --> 00:00:15,399
Why are you here again?

9
00:00:17,759 --> 00:00:18,759
I look forward to working with you.

10
00:00:25,226 --> 00:00:26,226
Bye then.

11
00:00:31,172 --> 00:00:32,580
Good morning, Team Manager.

12
00:00:35,179 --> 00:00:37,626
Don't do that. It's not cute at all.

13
00:00:38,146 --> 00:00:39,346
Why not?

14
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:42,166
Look closer. I might seem cuter.

15
00:00:43,559 --> 00:00:44,559
Seriously.

16
00:00:45,446 --> 00:00:46,446
Good morning.

17
00:00:47,849 --> 00:00:48,982
Hello, Chief Ko.

18
00:00:49,319 --> 00:00:50,452
Thank you for your leniency.

19
00:00:50,593 --> 00:00:53,153
Thanks to you, I'm out in the sun again.

20
00:00:54,732 --> 00:00:55,732
This feels new.

21
00:00:56,024 --> 00:00:57,224
Protests, trespassing,

22
00:00:57,493 --> 00:00:59,293
assault, theft.
That's all I've seen of you.

23
00:01:00,126 --> 00:01:02,829
Forget all those bad memories.

24
00:01:03,226 --> 00:01:04,759
I've been reborn thanks to you.

25
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:06,732
Nice to meet you, Cho Eun Ae.

26
00:01:07,159 --> 00:01:08,668
I'm Seo Seung Ri
from the Strategic Planning Team.

27
00:01:08,668 --> 00:01:10,559
How do you know me?

28
00:01:10,559 --> 00:01:13,073
We'll talk about that later.
Let's go in.

29
00:01:13,672 --> 00:01:14,672
Yes.

30
00:01:19,452 --> 00:01:20,593
I'm Cho Eun Ae.

31
00:01:20,593 --> 00:01:22,782
I'm determined to dedicate myself
to Kangsu Construction.

32
00:01:24,046 --> 00:01:26,146
What dedication for a six-month intern?

33
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,259
It's just a metaphor to say...

34
00:01:29,259 --> 00:01:31,059
I'll do my best, Team Manager.

35
00:01:32,461 --> 00:01:34,795
By the way, is Han Ji Hun not here yet?

36
00:01:38,046 --> 00:01:39,879
I'm sorry. Traffic was bad.

37
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:42,259
Being late on your first day isn't ideal.

38
00:01:42,926 --> 00:01:43,926
I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

39
00:01:44,326 --> 00:01:46,659
Hello, I'm Han Ji Hun. I've just joined...

40
00:01:46,659 --> 00:01:47,859
the Strategic Planning Team.

41
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:50,277
I'm Ko Gyeol, Team Two Manager.

42
00:01:51,193 --> 00:01:52,959
Hello, sir.
I look forward to working with you.

43
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:55,105
I'm Kim Seong Guk.

44
00:01:56,312 --> 00:01:58,479
I'm Ha Yu Ju, also on Team One.

45
00:02:00,492 --> 00:02:03,592
Well, the two new hires
don't need introductions, right?

46
00:02:05,559 --> 00:02:07,326
Cho Eun Ae?

47
00:02:07,726 --> 00:02:09,930
Hello, Mr. Han Ji Hun.

48
00:02:10,593 --> 00:02:13,199
All right, now that the teams are all set,

49
00:02:13,453 --> 00:02:14,519
let's give it our best.

50
00:02:15,059 --> 00:02:18,093
Team One,
gather in the meeting room in 30 minutes.

51
00:02:20,826 --> 00:02:22,309
Where is my seat?

52
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:23,543
It's over here, Ms. Cho.

53
00:02:23,543 --> 00:02:25,119
Yes, thank you.

54
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:31,718
Mr. Han, please sit over here.

55
00:02:32,906 --> 00:02:34,637
Sorry? Okay...

56
00:02:37,226 --> 00:02:38,226
Let's see.

57
00:02:41,893 --> 00:02:43,193
Just one month.

58
00:02:43,526 --> 00:02:45,619
Before that,
I'll completely and legally...

59
00:02:45,619 --> 00:02:47,460
take my babies back.

60
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:48,993
You're all done for.

61
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,673
I'm heading out for field work.

62
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:54,839
What? Field work?

63
00:02:55,558 --> 00:02:56,810
Yes. Why?

64
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,093
It's my first day today.

65
00:02:59,093 --> 00:03:01,493
Don't we have any meetings or anything?

66
00:03:01,493 --> 00:03:02,693
Any instructions?

67
00:03:02,693 --> 00:03:04,426
Instructions?

68
00:03:04,959 --> 00:03:06,626
First, get used to the company.

69
00:03:06,911 --> 00:03:09,064
The team manager
has been out on field work...

70
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:10,959
ever since his first day.

71
00:03:11,693 --> 00:03:14,459
You can leave once you're done.

72
00:03:16,585 --> 00:03:17,785
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, Mr. Han Ji Hun.

73
00:03:18,105 --> 00:03:19,959
You need to go through...

74
00:03:19,959 --> 00:03:21,493
the orientation period
as per company policy.

75
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:23,126
Orientation?

76
00:03:23,459 --> 00:03:25,526
I'll give you the materials to review,
so please wait.

77
00:03:30,426 --> 00:03:31,426
Let's talk.

78
00:03:31,593 --> 00:03:32,693
I'll wait by the emergency exit.

79
00:03:42,726 --> 00:03:43,726
What's your deal?

80
00:03:44,026 --> 00:03:45,059
Why are you here?

81
00:03:45,226 --> 00:03:47,626
Why? Am I not allowed to be here...

82
00:03:47,826 --> 00:03:49,359
while you are?

83
00:03:49,711 --> 00:03:51,449
That's not what I meant.

84
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:53,700
When I got scouted here,

85
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,193
they didn't say you'd be coming too.

86
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:57,971
Whatever. I'll give you my account number,
so transfer the money.

87
00:03:59,126 --> 00:04:00,126
Money?

88
00:04:01,026 --> 00:04:02,026
Right, the sale proceeds.

89
00:04:02,426 --> 00:04:03,426
I thought you didn't want it.

90
00:04:03,973 --> 00:04:06,301
You even tore up the check I gave you.

91
00:04:06,806 --> 00:04:09,450
That was because I wanted my company back.

92
00:04:10,006 --> 00:04:11,959
But now that I've given up
and joined Kangsu Construction,

93
00:04:11,959 --> 00:04:13,359
there's no reason not to take it.

94
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:16,757
So hand over half as my share.

95
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,192
Half?

96
00:04:19,453 --> 00:04:21,395
- All 250,000 dollars?
- Yes, all of it.

97
00:04:22,799 --> 00:04:24,166
If you don't send it within this week,

98
00:04:24,612 --> 00:04:26,466
I'll expose how you scammed me...

99
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:28,335
- and sold Joy to Kangsu Construction.
- Hey!

100
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:31,171
Calling it a scam is too much.

101
00:04:31,171 --> 00:04:32,426
You faked...

102
00:04:32,859 --> 00:04:35,126
a confession and a kiss, deceived me,

103
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:37,593
stole my seal, and sold my company.

104
00:04:37,593 --> 00:04:38,593
If that's not a scam, what is?

105
00:04:39,026 --> 00:04:40,981
I'll make sure you're blacklisted
in this industry.

106
00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:42,193
All right.

107
00:04:43,152 --> 00:04:44,152
I'll send it.

108
00:04:45,226 --> 00:04:48,126
I'll send it, so please.

109
00:04:49,846 --> 00:04:50,846
And from now on,

110
00:04:51,712 --> 00:04:53,656
don't speak casually to me.

111
00:04:53,993 --> 00:04:55,762
We joined at the same time.

112
00:04:57,526 --> 00:04:59,666
Do you understand, Mr. Han Ji Hun?

113
00:05:00,393 --> 00:05:01,459
All right, Eun Ae.

114
00:05:03,259 --> 00:05:04,626
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

115
00:05:15,207 --> 00:05:17,284
What if she really exposes everything?

116
00:05:24,305 --> 00:05:26,226
I heard a lot of unnecessary things.

117
00:05:28,979 --> 00:05:29,979
Wait a second.

118
00:05:30,363 --> 00:05:31,531
Answer me, now!

119
00:05:31,926 --> 00:05:33,226
What was that confession the other day?

120
00:05:33,226 --> 00:05:35,135
And what was that kiss supposed to mean?

121
00:05:36,559 --> 00:05:38,159
So that's what it was?

122
00:05:44,826 --> 00:05:47,014
Finally, I get to see my baby Joy again.

123
00:05:51,119 --> 00:05:52,753
When will they give me access
to the server?

124
00:05:53,106 --> 00:05:54,739
I can't ask on the first day.

125
00:05:56,559 --> 00:05:57,793
- Here are the materials.
- Thank you.

126
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:03,926
Those are the manuals
and company documents...

127
00:06:03,926 --> 00:06:05,526
you need to know
as a Kangsu Construction employee.

128
00:06:05,893 --> 00:06:07,426
For today, just go through those.

129
00:06:07,632 --> 00:06:08,768
Okay.

130
00:06:09,739 --> 00:06:10,906
By the way,

131
00:06:11,673 --> 00:06:13,807
when do we start development work?

132
00:06:14,143 --> 00:06:16,743
I told you, it's the orientation period.

133
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:20,046
Right, the orientation.

134
00:06:21,759 --> 00:06:23,559
Ji Seon isn't flying today?

135
00:06:24,266 --> 00:06:27,220
That's good.
Then come over for dinner tonight.

136
00:06:27,446 --> 00:06:29,572
Okay, I'll talk to her first.

137
00:06:29,572 --> 00:06:30,891
But what's the occasion?

138
00:06:31,213 --> 00:06:33,885
Eun Ae started
at Kangsu Construction today.

139
00:06:33,885 --> 00:06:36,230
What?
I thought she got an investment recently.

140
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,898
- What about her company?
- I don't know.

141
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:40,360
I like this
much better than that startup stuff.

142
00:06:40,659 --> 00:06:43,526
Nothing beats a stable salary.

143
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:44,872
Be here by 7 p.m.

144
00:06:47,466 --> 00:06:49,142
Bit Na, come out and have some apples.

145
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:57,083
Honey, Mom wants us
to have dinner together tonight.

146
00:06:58,012 --> 00:06:59,012
Okay, I'll go.

147
00:06:59,226 --> 00:07:02,026
Really? It's your day off.
Are you sure?

148
00:07:02,026 --> 00:07:03,259
We haven't visited in a while.

149
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:05,680
Thank you for saying that.

150
00:07:06,347 --> 00:07:07,780
It's nothing to thank me for.

151
00:07:08,879 --> 00:07:09,879
You're right.

152
00:07:10,599 --> 00:07:13,166
Sometimes,
I feel like I'm being irrational.

153
00:07:13,646 --> 00:07:14,646
Irrational?

154
00:07:15,486 --> 00:07:18,953
I still can't get used to
the way you talk.

155
00:07:19,306 --> 00:07:20,706
I'm used to it.

156
00:07:21,572 --> 00:07:22,572
What?

157
00:07:25,926 --> 00:07:28,459
Dad, what's the essence of this apple?

158
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:30,880
Something to eat.

159
00:07:34,372 --> 00:07:35,593
Now that I've eaten it...

160
00:07:35,593 --> 00:07:37,187
It's part of my body, right?

161
00:07:37,187 --> 00:07:38,958
We really do communicate well.

162
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:40,600
- Cross!
- Cross!

163
00:07:42,127 --> 00:07:43,296
Bit Na,

164
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,298
you're only skipping kindergarten today.

165
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,893
Why? If I don't go,

166
00:07:47,893 --> 00:07:51,093
you and Dad won't have to worry
about tuition.

167
00:07:51,626 --> 00:07:52,759
I won't go anymore.

168
00:07:53,975 --> 00:07:55,909
If you say that one more time,
you're in trouble.

169
00:07:56,126 --> 00:07:57,593
She's right, Bit Na.

170
00:07:57,593 --> 00:07:59,359
Leave the money worries to the adults,
okay?

171
00:07:59,359 --> 00:08:01,326
Okay.

172
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:08,421
(The air in the ER trembled.
Do Yeon's eyes shone as she ran...)

173
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,359
My goodness.

174
00:08:14,359 --> 00:08:17,259
Memorizing all these organs...

175
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:19,862
must be tough, Dr. Cho.

176
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:22,293
You're not going to school today?

177
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:25,305
No, class got canceled.

178
00:08:25,559 --> 00:08:27,941
Eun Hyeong's family is coming over later,

179
00:08:27,941 --> 00:08:30,039
so I'm going grocery shopping.
Want anything?

180
00:08:30,039 --> 00:08:31,039
No.

181
00:08:31,453 --> 00:08:34,386
All right, study hard.
Your exam is coming up.

182
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:40,585
Thanks, Dr. Cho.

183
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,331
- For what?
- Unlike your sister,

184
00:08:43,331 --> 00:08:45,592
you take good care of yourself.

185
00:08:56,225 --> 00:08:57,225
This won't do.

186
00:08:57,939 --> 00:09:00,940
I can't stay in my room while Mom cooks.

187
00:09:01,879 --> 00:09:02,879
I should get out.

188
00:09:03,993 --> 00:09:07,026
Eun Ae's lucky.
She even gets a celebration party.

189
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:09,383
You did well.

190
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:11,714
You were too harsh on her that day.

191
00:09:11,714 --> 00:09:12,715
What?

192
00:09:12,715 --> 00:09:15,322
Imagine if Cho Rong had been detained.

193
00:09:15,659 --> 00:09:16,893
Just thinking about it...

194
00:09:16,893 --> 00:09:19,559
still makes my heart race.

195
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:22,293
Actually, I thought about causing trouble
and going in after Eun Ae.

196
00:09:22,293 --> 00:09:23,959
- While visiting her.
- You brat!

197
00:09:24,684 --> 00:09:27,139
Don't say such awful things!

198
00:09:29,412 --> 00:09:31,890
You visited her in detention?

199
00:09:32,306 --> 00:09:34,117
You two were in this together.

200
00:09:38,766 --> 00:09:39,999
Is Bit Na's mom coming too?

201
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:43,550
She probably will. It's her day off.

202
00:09:44,073 --> 00:09:47,793
This dinner isn't just for Eun Ae.

203
00:09:47,793 --> 00:09:50,693
It's also
to help Bit Na's mom feel better.

204
00:09:51,726 --> 00:09:52,893
Like Cho Rong said,

205
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:55,526
she probably didn't want
her private life exposed.

206
00:09:55,526 --> 00:09:59,045
Still, Eun Ae must be impressive.

207
00:09:59,226 --> 00:10:01,826
A big company even recruited her.

208
00:10:01,826 --> 00:10:03,759
It's temporary, six months.

209
00:10:04,659 --> 00:10:07,359
But if she does well,

210
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,516
she might become a full-time employee.

211
00:10:09,926 --> 00:10:12,093
She will, for sure.

212
00:10:13,826 --> 00:10:14,826
Definitely!

213
00:10:15,259 --> 00:10:17,006
If they find out she got in
under false pretenses,

214
00:10:17,007 --> 00:10:18,426
there'll be another uproar.

215
00:10:19,021 --> 00:10:21,154
Just try siding with Eun Ae one more time.

216
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,800
Revenge is a long and difficult road.

217
00:10:28,573 --> 00:10:30,139
I have no money,

218
00:10:30,359 --> 00:10:32,498
but I wait for her at this cafe every day.

219
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,799
Why isn't she showing up?

220
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:38,126
Could she have figured out my plan
for revenge?

221
00:10:41,593 --> 00:10:42,593
She's finally here.

222
00:10:48,126 --> 00:10:50,093
My revenge begins now.

223
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:53,084
Fast and precise,

224
00:10:53,526 --> 00:10:55,254
I'll tear her heart to pieces...

225
00:10:58,859 --> 00:10:59,859
Commence the operation.

226
00:11:00,052 --> 00:11:01,752
Fly like a butterfly, sting like a...

227
00:11:02,926 --> 00:11:05,026
No, fly like a bee...

228
00:11:13,785 --> 00:11:14,826
Hello.

229
00:11:14,826 --> 00:11:16,459
- Would you like to order?
- Yes.

230
00:11:16,459 --> 00:11:17,693
An iced Americano.

231
00:11:33,259 --> 00:11:34,561
(Crazy girl)

232
00:11:43,272 --> 00:11:44,305
Why that...

233
00:11:46,993 --> 00:11:49,259
By now, her heart must be breaking.

234
00:11:50,026 --> 00:11:53,226
That crazy girl will keep chasing you
until you finish that notebook.

235
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,517
Hey, you perverted psycho!

236
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:08,728
What did you do to my notebook?

237
00:12:09,126 --> 00:12:10,259
Seriously.

238
00:12:11,686 --> 00:12:13,232
This is my sister's cardigan.

239
00:12:15,259 --> 00:12:16,326
What are you doing?

240
00:12:17,019 --> 00:12:18,204
You pervert!

241
00:12:22,452 --> 00:12:24,457
You slapped me again?

242
00:12:25,059 --> 00:12:26,445
Just you wait.

243
00:12:32,159 --> 00:12:35,488
Hello.
I'd like to report sexual harassment.

244
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:38,258
What? Sexual harassment?

245
00:12:40,253 --> 00:12:42,200
It depends on the camera angle,

246
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,268
but it doesn't seem like
there was any intent to sexually harass.

247
00:12:44,664 --> 00:12:46,499
Exactly.

248
00:12:47,359 --> 00:12:48,959
This is my sister's cardigan.

249
00:12:49,485 --> 00:12:50,885
And because of her...

250
00:12:51,426 --> 00:12:52,767
It got dirty like this. Look!

251
00:12:53,799 --> 00:12:55,699
I'm seriously being wronged here.

252
00:12:56,092 --> 00:12:57,901
It's totally unfair!

253
00:12:57,901 --> 00:13:00,593
Why would you wipe mud
on someone else's clothes?

254
00:13:01,259 --> 00:13:03,149
This guy really is a pervert.

255
00:13:03,474 --> 00:13:06,019
Last time, he was touching his own body...

256
00:13:06,034 --> 00:13:08,254
That's because I was drawing.

257
00:13:08,254 --> 00:13:10,223
I was feeling my muscles for reference.

258
00:13:10,223 --> 00:13:12,467
I needed a detailed depiction.

259
00:13:12,467 --> 00:13:14,794
You even grabbed my hand and squeezed it.

260
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:17,859
That's because you were wiping coffee
with my precious napkin!

261
00:13:19,239 --> 00:13:20,867
Officer,

262
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:23,460
last time she slapped me, and now again...

263
00:13:25,099 --> 00:13:27,940
I'm reporting her for assault.

264
00:13:28,809 --> 00:13:29,809
Assault?

265
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:30,926
Yes, assault!

266
00:13:31,293 --> 00:13:32,293
All right.

267
00:13:32,293 --> 00:13:34,959
It doesn't seem like sexual harassment,

268
00:13:35,406 --> 00:13:37,683
but it's understandable
how this could be misunderstood,

269
00:13:38,293 --> 00:13:40,059
- so please try to settle this amicably.
- I can't!

270
00:13:52,799 --> 00:13:55,001
(Kangsu Construction)

271
00:13:59,073 --> 00:14:00,373
I'll do it. Get some rest, Dad.

272
00:14:00,559 --> 00:14:01,993
What are you saying? It's my job.

273
00:14:01,993 --> 00:14:03,109
- Give it here.
- I'll do it.

274
00:14:07,059 --> 00:14:10,516
(Mom,
Family dinner at 7 p.m. tonight)

275
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,920
Hi, Mom. I just saw it.

276
00:14:14,459 --> 00:14:15,626
A party for my new job?

277
00:14:16,393 --> 00:14:18,059
Come on, it's not that big.

278
00:14:18,059 --> 00:14:19,393
There's another reason.

279
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:22,148
Your sister-in-law doesn't have
a flight today either.

280
00:14:23,172 --> 00:14:25,198
Try to come home early and help me.

281
00:14:25,427 --> 00:14:26,627
Okay, Mom.

282
00:14:29,265 --> 00:14:32,098
She may not show it,
but she cares about you a lot.

283
00:14:32,686 --> 00:14:33,852
I know.

284
00:14:35,059 --> 00:14:36,393
Hey, give it to me.

285
00:14:36,393 --> 00:14:37,859
I'll do it. Get some rest.

286
00:14:37,859 --> 00:14:39,759
- Just give it to me.
- I said I'll do it.

287
00:14:39,759 --> 00:14:40,993
- Give it here.
- Hey, Seong Jun.

288
00:14:41,448 --> 00:14:42,448
Dae Chi...

289
00:14:43,199 --> 00:14:44,832
Sir.

290
00:14:45,017 --> 00:14:47,265
Why so formal between us?

291
00:14:48,752 --> 00:14:50,223
You should say hello.

292
00:14:50,705 --> 00:14:52,725
He's my closest friend.

293
00:14:53,632 --> 00:14:54,632
What?

294
00:14:56,826 --> 00:14:58,559
Hello, I'm Ko Min Ho.

295
00:14:59,993 --> 00:15:01,493
So you have two sons.

296
00:15:02,926 --> 00:15:03,926
This is my daughter.

297
00:15:04,773 --> 00:15:06,139
She joined Strategic Planning today.

298
00:15:06,559 --> 00:15:08,426
Hello, I'm Cho Eun Ae.

299
00:15:09,046 --> 00:15:11,146
Wait, aren't you the one...

300
00:15:11,959 --> 00:15:15,126
who trespassed
into the CPO's office before?

301
00:15:15,853 --> 00:15:18,284
- That developer?
- Yes.

302
00:15:19,093 --> 00:15:21,093
I'm really sorry about what happened.

303
00:15:22,066 --> 00:15:23,799
Still, thank you again...

304
00:15:24,293 --> 00:15:25,725
for giving her this internship.

305
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:26,726
Not at all.

306
00:15:27,472 --> 00:15:30,196
I guess we were all meant to connect.

307
00:15:31,499 --> 00:15:33,099
Hey, take good care of her.

308
00:15:33,492 --> 00:15:34,626
Of course.

309
00:15:35,966 --> 00:15:36,966
Please work hard.

310
00:15:37,218 --> 00:15:39,272
Yes, sir. I'll do my best.

311
00:15:40,519 --> 00:15:43,386
It's almost lunchtime.
Let's grab lunch together.

312
00:15:43,612 --> 00:15:46,312
No, I still have the restroom to clean.

313
00:15:47,126 --> 00:15:49,482
Really?
Then let's eat next time when you're free.

314
00:15:50,566 --> 00:15:52,652
Take it easy. Bye.

315
00:15:52,959 --> 00:15:54,020
Bye.

316
00:16:00,913 --> 00:16:03,579
Why does the CEO have to be your friend?

317
00:16:04,139 --> 00:16:05,139
What?

318
00:16:06,254 --> 00:16:07,300
I will soon...

319
00:16:08,945 --> 00:16:10,978
Never mind,
I'll tell you when it's decided.

320
00:16:11,746 --> 00:16:13,779
I still have to finish cleaning,

321
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:16,160
so go have lunch with your co-workers.

322
00:16:28,526 --> 00:16:29,526
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

323
00:16:31,739 --> 00:16:32,859
Do you have some time?

324
00:16:33,165 --> 00:16:34,665
Sorry? Yes.

325
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:36,362
Come with me.

326
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,100
Okay.

327
00:16:48,319 --> 00:16:50,009
This place has a great vibe.

328
00:16:50,459 --> 00:16:52,559
Yes, it's near the office,

329
00:16:52,559 --> 00:16:53,913
and the food is pretty good too.

330
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:57,673
I'll tell you everything you need to know
for work.

331
00:16:58,359 --> 00:16:59,459
Thank you.

332
00:17:01,046 --> 00:17:04,413
You bought me a suit out of the blue.

333
00:17:05,631 --> 00:17:08,761
I don't know
if I should accept something like this.

334
00:17:09,098 --> 00:17:11,265
Startups and regular companies
are different.

335
00:17:12,093 --> 00:17:14,059
There's no strict rule,

336
00:17:14,659 --> 00:17:16,859
but coming to work
dressed like this every day is a bit...

337
00:17:18,113 --> 00:17:20,313
You mean I should follow TPO?

338
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:23,306
Dressing appropriately
for time, place, and occasion?

339
00:17:24,225 --> 00:17:25,258
Got it.

340
00:17:26,552 --> 00:17:28,085
The lunch course here is good.

341
00:17:28,326 --> 00:17:29,647
You can just pick your pasta.

342
00:17:29,647 --> 00:17:30,648
Really?

343
00:17:31,193 --> 00:17:33,440
I'll have the seafood tomato pasta.

344
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:35,859
Two lunch courses, please.

345
00:17:35,859 --> 00:17:37,859
One seafood tomato pasta
and one aglio e olio.

346
00:17:37,859 --> 00:17:38,893
Okay.

347
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,863
But why are you being so nice to me?

348
00:17:44,097 --> 00:17:45,464
- Me?
- Yes.

349
00:17:46,059 --> 00:17:48,493
At first, you seemed so cold and distant,

350
00:17:48,493 --> 00:17:49,893
like it'd be hard to even talk to you.

351
00:17:50,359 --> 00:17:53,393
But you're actually really nice,
so I don't know how to react.

352
00:17:54,139 --> 00:17:57,143
To be honest, I made a mistake.

353
00:17:57,466 --> 00:18:00,179
Sorry? A mistake?

354
00:18:00,646 --> 00:18:02,320
When we acquired Lucky Joy Tech,

355
00:18:02,586 --> 00:18:04,617
I made the decision
without meeting both CEOs.

356
00:18:05,466 --> 00:18:07,353
Given my position, that wasn't right.

357
00:18:08,459 --> 00:18:10,959
If we're talking about mistakes,
mine was the biggest.

358
00:18:11,766 --> 00:18:14,260
I didn't even try
to grasp the whole situation.

359
00:18:15,193 --> 00:18:17,596
It's all my fault,
so don't feel too sorry.

360
00:18:17,893 --> 00:18:19,359
Instead of feeling sorry,

361
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:22,026
as your senior,
it's natural for me to help you.

362
00:18:22,593 --> 00:18:23,593
Think of me as your mentor.

363
00:18:23,852 --> 00:18:25,285
A mentor?

364
00:18:26,478 --> 00:18:27,906
Thank you.

365
00:18:28,718 --> 00:18:31,025
About that incident before,

366
00:18:31,025 --> 00:18:32,812
did everything get resolved?

367
00:18:32,812 --> 00:18:33,845
Yes.

368
00:18:34,559 --> 00:18:37,717
Min Ho handled it well, very smoothly.

369
00:18:38,652 --> 00:18:40,085
Did something happen at the company?

370
00:18:40,373 --> 00:18:43,173
I didn't handle it alone.
Gyeol helped too.

371
00:18:43,459 --> 00:18:45,726
But why isn't Gyeol back yet?

372
00:18:46,346 --> 00:18:47,627
Didn't you leave together?

373
00:18:47,859 --> 00:18:50,663
He went out right after coming in
this morning and hasn't been back.

374
00:18:51,193 --> 00:18:53,700
- What?
- Why is he like that?

375
00:18:53,926 --> 00:18:56,426
Even if it's his grandfather's company,
he can't just do whatever he wants.

376
00:18:56,736 --> 00:18:57,736
I'm home.

377
00:18:57,912 --> 00:18:59,338
Welcome back.

378
00:18:59,819 --> 00:19:00,826
Did you eat dinner?

379
00:19:00,826 --> 00:19:02,708
Yes, I had something light outside.

380
00:19:04,152 --> 00:19:05,152
Sit down for a moment.

381
00:19:05,459 --> 00:19:06,459
Okay.

382
00:19:10,626 --> 00:19:11,626
Right, Father.

383
00:19:12,859 --> 00:19:16,126
You remember my high school friend
Seong Jun, right?

384
00:19:16,206 --> 00:19:17,990
Of course, I remember.

385
00:19:18,906 --> 00:19:20,027
You remember too, right?

386
00:19:20,646 --> 00:19:21,993
I'm not sure.

387
00:19:21,993 --> 00:19:26,093
You know, the top student...

388
00:19:26,093 --> 00:19:27,936
who used to come here for tutoring...

389
00:19:27,936 --> 00:19:29,713
with Mr. Seo.

390
00:19:29,713 --> 00:19:30,926
I remember.

391
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:35,074
He always came early
and studied in advance.

392
00:19:35,074 --> 00:19:38,393
Why did you lose touch with him?

393
00:19:39,193 --> 00:19:41,994
We recently met again at the company.

394
00:19:41,994 --> 00:19:44,784
The top student who's now a cleaner?

395
00:19:45,972 --> 00:19:47,093
What are you talking about?

396
00:19:47,093 --> 00:19:49,393
He graduated
from Korea University's Business School...

397
00:19:49,393 --> 00:19:51,586
and even worked as an executive
at Samho Group.

398
00:19:52,194 --> 00:19:54,660
But I think he got laid off last year.

399
00:19:56,426 --> 00:19:58,030
Such a talented person.

400
00:19:58,633 --> 00:20:01,066
I used to wonder about him
from time to time.

401
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:06,324
If it's meant to be, you'll meet again.

402
00:20:07,126 --> 00:20:08,126
Mr. Ju,

403
00:20:08,485 --> 00:20:10,809
if you're done cleaning the leaves,
you can go downstairs.

404
00:20:11,493 --> 00:20:12,659
You usually go to bed early.

405
00:20:12,659 --> 00:20:14,193
Why have you been wiping leaves
for an hour?

406
00:20:15,399 --> 00:20:17,278
All right, let's get up.

407
00:20:18,093 --> 00:20:19,926
Gyeol, come to my room for a moment.

408
00:20:21,193 --> 00:20:22,259
Yes, Grandpa.

409
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:30,913
So, where were you all day
instead of being at the office?

410
00:20:35,405 --> 00:20:36,572
Were you out taking photos?

411
00:20:37,213 --> 00:20:40,409
Yes, I took photos
and did a few other things.

412
00:20:40,825 --> 00:20:41,825
Good.

413
00:20:42,539 --> 00:20:43,973
Architecture is also an art.

414
00:20:44,459 --> 00:20:47,593
You won't get good results
just sitting in an office.

415
00:20:48,619 --> 00:20:52,519
I watched your father work up close
many times.

416
00:20:53,687 --> 00:20:54,687
Yes.

417
00:20:55,119 --> 00:20:57,948
But why did you eat before coming home?

418
00:20:58,526 --> 00:20:59,693
Are you still uncomfortable?

419
00:21:00,326 --> 00:21:01,359
No, it's nothing like that.

420
00:21:01,627 --> 00:21:04,841
It won't be easy,

421
00:21:06,053 --> 00:21:08,400
but you should be the one
to open up to the family first.

422
00:21:09,159 --> 00:21:11,070
That's how people come
to understand each other.

423
00:21:11,819 --> 00:21:13,676
Don't keep staying away from home.

424
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:16,709
Take it as your grandpa's request.

425
00:21:17,613 --> 00:21:19,477
Yes, I'll keep that in mind.

426
00:21:20,292 --> 00:21:23,659
And while you're out taking photos,

427
00:21:24,493 --> 00:21:26,626
find a place with nice air and flowers.

428
00:21:27,213 --> 00:21:30,079
I'm planning to go on a date
with your grandma.

429
00:21:32,326 --> 00:21:34,968
That's a great idea. I'll look into it.

430
00:21:35,866 --> 00:21:38,632
Also, get yourself a car.

431
00:21:39,372 --> 00:21:40,706
You'll need mobility...

432
00:21:41,259 --> 00:21:44,259
to commute and go around for site visits.

433
00:21:44,899 --> 00:21:47,232
No, I don't even have a driver's license.

434
00:21:48,152 --> 00:21:49,152
What?

435
00:21:49,793 --> 00:21:51,327
You still don't have one?

436
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:55,112
Then how did you live in the U.S.?

437
00:21:55,932 --> 00:21:56,999
There's public transportation,

438
00:21:57,586 --> 00:21:58,886
and I'm good at riding a bike.

439
00:22:03,779 --> 00:22:06,246
How are Min Ho and Gyeol doing
at the company?

440
00:22:07,459 --> 00:22:09,426
Chief Ko works hard,

441
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:11,573
but I'm not sure about Gyeol.

442
00:22:12,859 --> 00:22:14,466
He's hardly ever at the office.

443
00:22:14,466 --> 00:22:16,499
That's all intentional.

444
00:22:17,593 --> 00:22:18,659
Look at historical dramas.

445
00:22:19,159 --> 00:22:21,288
A prince who's smarter
than the crown prince...

446
00:22:21,288 --> 00:22:22,879
never lived long.

447
00:22:23,726 --> 00:22:26,026
He's deliberately holding back.

448
00:22:26,026 --> 00:22:28,726
You watch too many dramas.

449
00:22:30,106 --> 00:22:32,113
Why isn't Seung Wu coming to eat?

450
00:22:32,479 --> 00:22:34,754
Seo Seung Wu, come eat!

451
00:22:36,766 --> 00:22:38,859
He's not here? I'll go get him.

452
00:22:38,859 --> 00:22:39,861
Okay.

453
00:22:40,393 --> 00:22:42,593
Die!

454
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:47,912
Die!

455
00:22:47,912 --> 00:22:49,015
- Seo Seung Wu.
- You startled me.

456
00:22:49,365 --> 00:22:50,532
- What are you doing?
- Sorry?

457
00:22:52,899 --> 00:22:54,139
Nothing.

458
00:22:54,853 --> 00:22:57,343
Is that for your webtoon?

459
00:22:57,472 --> 00:23:00,112
Yes, my next story is a revenge plot.

460
00:23:00,952 --> 00:23:03,148
It's going to be intense and hardcore.

461
00:23:04,452 --> 00:23:06,452
Have you finished the piece
for the contest?

462
00:23:06,626 --> 00:23:09,588
Yes, I'll just revise it one more time
before submitting.

463
00:23:12,626 --> 00:23:14,226
"Secretary by Nature?"

464
00:23:16,859 --> 00:23:17,859
Let's go, Dad.

465
00:23:20,199 --> 00:23:21,432
I don't even have the strength
to lift a spoon,

466
00:23:22,293 --> 00:23:23,295
but I'm starving.

467
00:23:26,472 --> 00:23:28,307
("Secretary by Nature")

468
00:23:36,885 --> 00:23:39,118
What's wrong? Did you hurt your arm?

469
00:23:39,659 --> 00:23:42,455
No, I just overused my right hand.

470
00:23:44,158 --> 00:23:45,691
What happened with the contest submission?

471
00:23:45,893 --> 00:23:46,893
He's not submitting it this time.

472
00:23:47,379 --> 00:23:49,738
I saw it, and it's not good enough
for a contest.

473
00:23:50,359 --> 00:23:51,418
Seo Seung Ri!

474
00:23:51,797 --> 00:23:53,666
What did you just say?

475
00:23:53,893 --> 00:23:55,425
Are you going to keep this up?

476
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,193
Why are you belittling my work like that?

477
00:23:59,199 --> 00:24:02,493
You shouldn't dismiss a piece
the author poured his heart into.

478
00:24:02,493 --> 00:24:05,993
If you fail again this time,
it's not your path.

479
00:24:06,453 --> 00:24:08,247
You can dig for ten years,
but if there's no water,

480
00:24:08,615 --> 00:24:10,449
it's just wasted effort.

481
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:12,626
I'll definitely win this contest...

482
00:24:12,626 --> 00:24:14,753
and get back at Mom and you.

483
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:18,791
I've got too many people to get back at.

484
00:24:19,873 --> 00:24:20,873
I'm exhausted.

485
00:24:25,859 --> 00:24:27,793
You're adorable.

486
00:24:27,793 --> 00:24:29,190
I'm home.

487
00:24:29,190 --> 00:24:30,559
- Hey.
- Hey, Eun Hyeong.

488
00:24:30,726 --> 00:24:31,993
Bit Na!

489
00:24:31,993 --> 00:24:33,043
Auntie.

490
00:24:34,226 --> 00:24:37,042
I almost forgot your face.
It's been so long.

491
00:24:37,193 --> 00:24:38,226
It's been a while.

492
00:24:38,339 --> 00:24:40,539
That just means she's been working hard.

493
00:24:41,559 --> 00:24:43,259
After dinner, come upstairs, Eun Hyeong.

494
00:24:43,259 --> 00:24:44,593
- We need to talk about that.
- What?

495
00:24:44,926 --> 00:24:46,126
Mom and Dad's trip.

496
00:24:46,826 --> 00:24:47,826
Okay.

497
00:24:50,419 --> 00:24:52,553
Bit Na, who did your hair?

498
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:54,926
Do you need help?

499
00:24:55,466 --> 00:24:58,472
No, you're finally off from flying.

500
00:24:58,472 --> 00:24:59,498
Just go rest.

501
00:25:00,126 --> 00:25:01,934
I just got off work too.

502
00:25:02,493 --> 00:25:03,493
It's getting burnt.

503
00:25:03,493 --> 00:25:05,270
You can't even do that properly?

504
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:07,940
Congratulations, Eun Ae.
I heard you joined Kangsu Construction.

505
00:25:07,940 --> 00:25:10,026
It's just an internship.

506
00:25:12,612 --> 00:25:15,380
Grandma,
the japchae and bulgogi are delicious.

507
00:25:16,499 --> 00:25:18,751
Really? I packed some for you,

508
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:20,363
so take it home and enjoy it.

509
00:25:20,363 --> 00:25:21,363
Okay.

510
00:25:21,363 --> 00:25:22,821
But why did you suddenly get a job?

511
00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:24,726
Well...

512
00:25:24,726 --> 00:25:27,226
It's a long story. I'll tell you later.

513
00:25:27,226 --> 00:25:28,694
There's nothing to hear.

514
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:31,159
Don't think too much about it.

515
00:25:31,159 --> 00:25:33,999
Just stay at Kangsu Construction
until you retire.

516
00:25:37,326 --> 00:25:39,226
Does the food not suit your taste?

517
00:25:39,226 --> 00:25:41,193
Why are you eating so little?

518
00:25:44,273 --> 00:25:46,489
I have something to say...

519
00:25:47,026 --> 00:25:48,380
in front of everyone.

520
00:25:49,884 --> 00:25:51,884
Go ahead. What is it?

521
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:55,612
I heard you're going on a trip
to Europe soon.

522
00:25:57,726 --> 00:26:00,826
It would be right for us
to cover the expenses,

523
00:26:02,106 --> 00:26:05,564
but we're not in a position to do that.
I'm so sorry.

524
00:26:05,973 --> 00:26:08,460
You don't need to worry about that at all.

525
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:10,393
I've already saved up for it.

526
00:26:10,759 --> 00:26:12,293
Thank you for understanding.

527
00:26:12,606 --> 00:26:15,074
Also,
there's something everyone should know.

528
00:26:19,382 --> 00:26:22,815
Eun Hyeong didn't get the position.

529
00:26:22,815 --> 00:26:23,841
Ji Seon.

530
00:26:25,206 --> 00:26:26,206
What?

531
00:26:26,459 --> 00:26:27,759
The Philosophy Department
is shutting down,

532
00:26:28,222 --> 00:26:29,822
so by next month, he'll be unemployed.

533
00:26:31,013 --> 00:26:33,125
What are you talking about?

534
00:26:34,213 --> 00:26:35,213
Unemployed?

535
00:26:59,818 --> 00:27:02,821
(Our Happy Days)

536
00:27:02,945 --> 00:27:04,759
What's wrong with all of you?

537
00:27:04,759 --> 00:27:07,226
Do you think
I'm that unreasonable and thoughtless?

538
00:27:07,393 --> 00:27:08,393
Don't follow me.

539
00:27:08,805 --> 00:27:12,072
What if Mom finds out
about your situation too, Dad?

540
00:27:12,559 --> 00:27:13,888
Good morning.

541
00:27:13,888 --> 00:27:15,400
Ms. Cho.

542
00:27:15,559 --> 00:27:16,826
Are you the same person as yesterday?

543
00:27:17,035 --> 00:27:18,559
Don't tell me you're going out again.

544
00:27:18,559 --> 00:27:20,932
Are you really not going to tell me
where you're going?

545
00:27:22,706 --> 00:27:23,706
It's a trade secret.

546
00:27:24,193 --> 00:27:25,793
Did you move the water bottle
that was here?

547
00:27:25,793 --> 00:27:27,923
Just stand there.
That's still the front row.

548
00:27:27,923 --> 00:27:30,193
What? I have to be in the center!

549
00:27:30,193 --> 00:27:32,831
- Move.
- What a strange woman!

550
00:27:33,285 --> 00:27:35,286
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
